polypeptide.name: Vitamin B12 transporter BtuB
polypeptide.specific-function: Involved in the active translocation of vitamin B12 (cyanocobalamin) across the outer membrane to the periplasmic space. It derives its energy for transport by interacting with the trans-periplasmic membrane protein TonB. Is also a receptor for bacteriophages BF23 and C1, and for A and E colicins.

polypeptide.name: Colipase
polypeptide.specific-function: Colipase is a cofactor of pancreatic lipase. It allows the lipase to anchor itself to the lipid-water interface. Without colipase the enzyme is washed off by bile salts, which have an inhibitory effect on the lipase.Enterostatin has a biological activity as a satiety signal.

polypeptide.specific-function: Photoreceptor required for image-forming vision at low light intensity. Required for photoreceptor cell viability after birth. polypeptide.name: Outer membrane usher protein PapC
polypeptide.specific-function: Involved in the export and assembly of pili subunits across the outer membrane. Forms a hexameric ring-shaped pore in the outer bacterial membrane. The 2 nanometer-diameter pore allows the passage of the thin tip fibrillum. As for the rod, it probably unwinds into linear fibers which would therefore be narrow enough to pass through the pore.

polypeptide.name: Esterase EstA
polypeptide.specific-function: Esterase whose enzymatic activity is required for rhamnolipid production, all kinds of cell motility (swimming, swarming, and twitching), and biofilm formation; the exact role of EstA in these processes is unclear. In vitro, has pronounced esterase activities towards p-nitrophenyl esters of short acyl chain length (C4-C6) and Tween detergents. Also shows relatively high activity towards beta-naphthyl butyrate, whereas its activities towards triacylglycerols and acyls-CoA are negligible.
polypeptide.organism: Pseudomonas aeruginosa (strain ATCC 15692 / PAO1 / 1C / PRS 101 / LMG 12228)
